adjectives.description: spookish (comparative more spookish, superlative most spookish)

entries.meaning: (informal) Frightening or unnerving in the manner of something eerie or supernatural; spooky.
examples: I hope we find some nicer spot than this. This looks so lonely and spookish.

entries.meaning: (informal, often of a horse or other animal) Easily startled, frightened, or unnerved.
examples: As a lesson horse she needs to gain confidence in her rider, or can become spookish over the jumps, dodging out of them.
